abstract: Wall Street's main stock indexes ended modestly higher on Wednesday after the U.S. Federal Reserve held interest rates steady and signaled that borrowing costs are likely to remain unchanged indefinitely.
snippet: Wall Street's main stock indexes ended modestly higher on Wednesday after the U.S. Federal Reserve held interest rates steady and signaled that borrowing costs are likely to remain unchanged indefinitely.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Wall Street's main stock indexes ended modestly higher on Wednesday after the U.S. Federal Reserve held interest rates steady and signaled that borrowing costs are likely to remain unchanged indefinitely.
headline_main: Wall Street Posts Modest Gain as Fed Signals Rates to Hold for Some Time
headline_print_headline: Wall Street Posts Modest Gain as Fed Signals Rates to Hold for Some Time

abstract: Greta Thunberg, the 16-year-old Swede who inspired millions of young people to take action against climate change, has been named Time Magazine's Person of the Year for 2019.
snippet: Greta Thunberg, the 16-year-old Swede who inspired millions of young people to take action against climate change, has been named Time Magazine's Person of the Year for 2019.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK/MADRID — Greta Thunberg, the 16-year-old Swede who inspired millions of young people to take action against climate change, has been named Time Magazine's Person of the Year for 2019.
headline_main: Teenage Climate Activist Greta Thunberg Is Time's Person of the Year
headline_print_headline: Teenage Climate Activist Greta Thunberg Is Time's Person of the Year

abstract: Higher energy prices lifted U.S. overall consumer prices in November.
snippet: Higher energy prices lifted U.S. overall consumer prices in November.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Higher energy prices lifted U.S. overall consumer prices in November.
headline_main: November US Consumer Prices Up 0.3% on Rising Energy Costs
headline_print_headline: November US Consumer Prices Up 0.3% on Rising Energy Costs

abstract: A$AP Rocky is back in Sweden. The American rapper performed Wednesday evening, four months after he was convicted of assault for a violent street brawl.
snippet: A$AP Rocky is back in Sweden. The American rapper performed Wednesday evening, four months after he was convicted of assault for a violent street brawl.
lead_paragraph: STOCKHOLM — A$AP Rocky is back in Sweden. The American rapper performed Wednesday evening, four months after he was convicted of assault for a violent street brawl.
headline_main: A$AP Rocky to Perform in Stockholm Months After Conviction

abstract: Iran's telecommunications minister announced on Wednesday that the country has defused a massive cyberattack on unspecified “electronic infrastructure" but provided no specifics on the purported attack.
snippet: Iran's telecommunications minister announced on Wednesday that the country has defused a massive cyberattack on unspecified “electronic infrastructure" but provided no specifics on the purported attack.
lead_paragraph: TEHRAN, Iran — Iran's telecommunications minister announced on Wednesday that the country has defused a massive cyberattack on unspecified “electronic infrastructure" but provided no specifics on the purported attack.
headline_main: Iran Says It's Defused Large Cyberattack on Infrastructure
headline_print_headline: Iran Says It's Defused Large Cyberattack on Infrastructure

abstract: Democrats in the U.S. House of Representatives moved closer on Wednesday to impeaching President Donald Trump as a key House committee began debating formal articles of impeachment that are expected to be brought to the House floor next week.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats in the U.S. House of Representatives moved closer on Wednesday to impeaching President Donald Trump as a key House committee began debating formal articles of impeachment that are expected to be brought to the House floor next week.
headline_main: U.S. Lawmakers Begin Debating Impeachment Articles Against Trump
headline_print_headline: U.S. Lawmakers Begin Debating Impeachment Articles Against Trump

abstract: The U.S.-China trade war is creating something William Gagnon once thought impossible - a 100% American-made bathroom hand dryer.

lead_paragraph: EAST LONGMEADOW, Mass. — The U.S.-China trade war is creating something William Gagnon once thought impossible - a 100% American-made bathroom hand dryer.

abstract: Iran has foiled a major cyber attack on its infrastructure that was launched by a foreign government, the Iranian telecoms minister said on Wednesday, two months after reports of a U.S. cyber operation against the country.
snippet: Iran has foiled a major cyber attack on its infrastructure that was launched by a foreign government, the Iranian telecoms minister said on Wednesday, two months after reports of a U.S. cyber operation against the country.
lead_paragraph: DUBAI — Iran has foiled a major cyber attack on its infrastructure that was launched by a foreign government, the Iranian telecoms minister said on Wednesday, two months after reports of a U.S. cyber operation against the country.
headline_main: Iran Says It Foiled 'Very Big' Foreign Cyber Attack
headline_print_headline: Iran Says It Foiled 'Very Big' Foreign Cyber Attack

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump will be the one to make the final decision on tariffs and the U.S.-China trade deal, White House trade adviser Peter Navarro said on Tuesday.
